x4freetext: Silicon surface barrier detector and a
diffusion drift detector with a sensitive layer from
AgS and InS (S-34) films with the thickness no more
than 0.3 and 0.7 mg/cm2, correspondingly, were used.
The films of AgS were prepared by evaporation of S-34
To obtain absolute differential cross-sections the
solid angles of the detectors were defined by
Rutherford scattering of alpha particles on gold leaf.
